The paper deals with low-complexity algorithms for beam and channel tracking for millimeter-wave (mmWave) communications, which are typically studied in the fields of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on the least mean squares (LMS) and bidirectional LMS (BiLMS) algorithms for a mobile mmWave transmission scenario, which are relevant to all of these sub-categories.
